<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="91" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="91">
Reported on the Cook Islands by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodkinson, ID" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="341 - 377" title="The psyllids (Homoptera: Psylloidea) of the Austro-Oriental, Pacific and Hawaiian zoogeographical realms: an annotated check list." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222938300770251" volume="17" year="1983">Hodkinson (1983)</bibRefCitation>
. Known from Rarotonga and Mangaia. Other locations include: Australia (
<bibRefCitation author="Hollis, D" journalOrPublisher="Australian Biological Resources Study, Canberra (Australia)" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" title="Australian Psylloidea. Jumping plantlice and lerp insects." year="2004">Hollis 2004</bibRefCitation>
), Africa [Cameroon, Democratic Republic of the Congo, Kenya, Madagascar, Seychelles, South Africa, Tanzania, Uganda and Zimbabwe (
<bibRefCitation author="Yana, W" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Biodiversity and Environmental Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 20" title="Jumping plant lice of the family Carsidaridae (Hemiptera: Psylloidea) from Cameroon: taxonomic, faunistic, phenology and host plants." volume="6" year="2015">Yana et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Burckhardt, D" journalOrPublisher="Fauna of Arabia" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="189 - 216" title="Jumping plant-lice (Insecta: Hemiptera: Psylloidea) of Yemen." volume="21" year="2006">Burckhardt and Van Harten 2006</bibRefCitation>
)], Asia [Chagos archipelago, China, India, Japan, Malaya, Malaysia, Mauritius, Philippines, Ryukyu Islands, Singapore, Yemen (
<bibRefCitation author="Hodkinson, ID" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="341 - 377" title="The psyllids (Homoptera: Psylloidea) of the Austro-Oriental, Pacific and Hawaiian zoogeographical realms: an annotated check list." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222938300770251" volume="17" year="1983">Hodkinson 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Hodkinson, ID" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="299 - 357" title="The psyllids (Homoptera: Psylloidea) of the Oriental Zoogeographical Region: an annotated check-list." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222938600770251" volume="20" year="1986">Hodkinson 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Burckhardt, D" journalOrPublisher="Fauna of Arabia" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="189 - 216" title="Jumping plant-lice (Insecta: Hemiptera: Psylloidea) of Yemen." volume="21" year="2006">Burckhardt and Van Harten 2006</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Percy, DM" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="1 - 163" title="Making the most of your host: the Metrosideros-feeding psyllids (Hemiptera: Psylloidea) of the Hawaiian Islands." url="https://doi.org/10.3897/zookeys.649.10213" volume="649" year="2017">Percy 2017</bibRefCitation>
)], Pacific Islands [Bismarck Archipelago, Caroline Islands, Fiji, French Polynesia (Australs, Societies, Marquesas), Gilbert Islands, New Caledonia, Palau, Tonga, Solomon Islands, Vanuatu (
<bibRefCitation author="Hodkinson, ID" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="91" pagination="341 - 377" title="The psyllids (Homoptera: Psylloidea) of the Austro-Oriental, Pacific and Hawaiian zoogeographical realms: an annotated check list." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222938300770251" volume="17" year="1983">Hodkinson 1983</bibRefCitation>
)].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
